            <offset>0</offset>
            <sentence>
                <offset>0</offset>
                <text>Given the diagnosis in the older brother, radiographs were taken of his younger sister (Patient 3) at age 4 months.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>116</offset>
                <text>Prior to these exams, the parents had not suspected that the second child might have the same disorder as her brother.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>235</offset>
                <text>However, on radiographic examination, there was a generalized epiphyseal dysplasia (no platyspondyly or coronal clefts) (Fig. 1).</text>
                <annotation id="1">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0002656</infon>
                    <location length="20" offset="62"/>
                    <text>epiphyseal dysplasia</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>365</offset>
                <text>She had a somewhat flat face but this was consistent with her ethnic origin and the ears were mildly cupped but not clearly dysmorphic.</text>
                <annotation id="2">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0012368</infon>
                    <location length="9" offset="19"/>
                    <text>flat face</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="3">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="4" offset="84"/>
                    <text>ears</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="4">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <location length="6" offset="101"/>
                    <text>cupped</text>
                </annotation>
                <relation id="5">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.PhenotypeRelations</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000378</infon>
                    <node refid="3" role="source"/>
                    <node refid="4" role="target"/>
                </relation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>501</offset>
                <text>An eye examination performed at 4 months of age showed no cataracts but a repeat exam at 7 months of age detected bilateral lens opacities with the left side requiring surgical correction.</text>
                <annotation id="6">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000518</infon>
                    <location length="14" offset="124"/>
                    <text>lens opacities</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>690</offset>
                <text>She had delayed motor milestones (standing at 26 months, ability to take one or two steps independently at 3.5 years) and delayed speech.</text>
                <annotation id="7">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0001270</infon>
                    <location length="24" offset="8"/>
                    <text>delayed motor milestones</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="8">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000750</infon>
                    <location length="14" offset="122"/>
                    <text>delayed speech</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>828</offset>
                <text>Cerebral MRIs at 7 months and at 2 years were normal.</text>
            </sentence>
        </passage>
